[Name]  setserial
[Summary]  A utility for configuring serial ports
[Description]  Setserial is a basic system utility for displaying or setting serial port information. Setserial can reveal and allow you to alter the I/O port and IRQ that a particular serial device is using.
[Suse Category]  Hardware/Other
[License]  GPL
[Homepage]  http://setserial.sourceforge.net
